{{Quote|For the first time in my life, I'm proud to wear this [[Wolverine Suit|suit]]. It means I'm an [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Man]]. I am the X-Man.|Wolverine to [[Deadpool]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
'''{{Conjecture|James Howlett}}''', more commonly referred to as '''Logan''', is a formidable [[mutant]] with retractable [[adamantium]] claws and regenerative abilities operating under the alias '''Wolverine''', who failed both his teammates, the [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Men]], and his world, sending him into a depressive spiral. He was taken from his [[Mutant Genocide Universe|universe]] by [[Deadpool]] in the latter's attempt to replace his own [[Earth-10005|reality]]'s [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]], though the two were banished to the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]] by [[Mr. Paradox]]'s [[Mr. Paradox's Crew|rogue faction]] of [[Time Variance Authority]] agents. Wolverine and Deadpool formed an initially very uneasy alliance to try and escape the Void, which they did with the aid of the [[Resistance]]. Now together as friends, the pair was able to stop Paradox's plan to destroy Deadpool's timeline and eliminate [[Cassandra Nova]] to save the entire [[Multiverse]], eventually allowing Logan to come to better terms with his past mistakes and live peacefully in Wade Wilson's universe.

==Biography==
{{MD|James Howlett (Earth-TRN1400)}}
===Early Life===
====Wolverine Origins====
{{Quote|The [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]]... He was a hero in [[Earth-10005|my world]]."<br>"Yeah, well, he ain't shit in [[Mutant Genocide Universe|mine]].|[[Deadpool]] and Wolverine|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
[[File:Wolverine Memory (X2 Archive Footage).png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Adamantium]] is fused to Logan's skeleton]]
Logan was a [[Canada|Canadian]]-born [[mutant]] who developed a regenerative healing factor as well as retractable claws, and eventually, [[adamantium]] was fused onto his bones during an intensely painful and brutal experiment. Due to his healing factor, he had lived for over two hundred years, and over the years, he had many violent encounters and eventually became something of an alcoholic and a recluse.
[[File:Wolverine vs. HYDRA (X2 Archive Footage).png|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine killing enemies in the [[X-Mansion]]]]
He often allied with the [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Men]], [[Professor X/Mutant Genocide|Charles Xavier]]'s team of mutant superheroes, and became known as Wolverine. All his teammates whom he befriended, including [[Cyclops/Mutant Genocide|Cyclops]], [[Jean Grey]], [[Storm/Mutant Genocide|Storm]] and [[Beast/Mutant Genocide|Beast]], offered Logan the [[Wolverine Suit]] and begged him to wear it to be part of the team, though he rejected it and called their own outfits ridiculous in an effort to have them not think he wanted to be there.{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Massacre at the X-Mansion|Death of the X-Men]]====
{{Quote|[[Cyclops/Mutant Genocide|Scott]] used to beg me to wear [[Wolverine Suit|it]]. So did [[Jean Grey|Jean]], [[Storm/Mutant Genocide|Storm]], [[Beast/Mutant Genocide|Beast]]... All of [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|them]]. They wanted me to be part of the team, but I wouldn't. Told them they all looked fuckin' ridiculous. I mean, I couldn't have 'em thinking I wanted to be there. And then one day while I was off on my own, the [[humans]] came. They went [[mutant]] hunting."<br>"I can guess the rest."<br>"No, no, let me say it, I... I need to say it. By the time I stumbled [[X-Mansion|home]], shit-faced from the bar, it was too late. They were dead.|Logan and [[Laura]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
One day, a drunken Logan returned to the [[X-Mansion]] to find that, while he was gone, [[humans]] who had hated and feared [[mutant]]-kind orchestrated a surprise attack on the X-Mansion, resulting in all the other [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Men]] and numerous mutants being murdered. Due to Logan's absence during the attack, he took the blame for their deaths upon himself and went on a violent rampage, killing those who were and were not involved in the slaughtering of his teammates. By the time he calmed down and regained his senses, the X-Men name had been tarnished and Logan was shunned by society for his actions, resulting in him growing into a state of heavy depression. He began wearing the [[Wolverine Suit]] at all times underneath his regular clothes, as it was the only memento of his teammates and actions.{{Ref|DW}}

===[[Preservation of Earth-10005]]===
====[[Search for Wolverine|Taken from His World]]====
[[File:Deadpool and Logan at a bar.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Logan confronts [[Deadpool]]]]
{{Quote|Why would I go with you?"<br>"Because, unfortunately, I need you. And even more unfortunately, my [[Earth-10005|entire world]] needs you.|Logan and [[Deadpool]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
By a bar's counter, Logan was given another drink by a bartender who eagerly wanted him gone. Logan was approached by [[Deadpool]], also known as Wade Wilson, a person who claimed to know him and to need him for his [[Earth-10005|world]]. Questioned by the bartender if they are going to fuck or fight, Logan did not react to the insult, much to Deadpool's surprise. Remarking that any other Wolverine would have hurt him by now and that he had little time, Deadpool raised Logan up from his seat, to which Logan responding by popping his claws. His claws had grown miniscule, as Deadpool sarcastically noted before putting a [[Deadpool's Twin Guns|gun]] to Logan's head. Logan simply laughed, drinking a whole bottle of whiskey while holding the gun for Deadpool to watch before collapsing to the floor.
[[File:Deadpool and Wolverine at the TVA.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine rises behind [[Deadpool]]]]
An unconscious Logan was taken into the [[Time Variance Authority Office]] through a [[Timedoor]] only dressed in his [[Wolverine Suit|suit]], falling on the floor yet hearing Deadpool and [[Time Variance Authority]] agent [[Mr. Paradox]]'s conversation about the impossibility of replacing what is known as an "Anchor Being," which was Deadpool's timeline's own Wolverine and Deadpool's actions to do so. Logan eventually rose up and was welcomed into the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] by Deadpool, albeit at a "low point." Deadpool went on to threaten Paradox by alerting his bosses, only to find out that they do not know. Logan was confused to see Deadpool pruned by a [[Time Stick]], which he was as well in his attempt to harm Paradox.{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Duel in the Void|Fight in the Void]]====
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (34).png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine furiously confronting [[Deadpool]]]]
{{Quote|Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait! I can fix it! I can fix it."<br>"Fix what?"<br>"Whatever it is you did. Whatever made you so bad.|[[Deadpool]] and Wolverine|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Wolverine approached an awakening [[Deadpool]] in a [[Void (End of Time)|barren wasteland]], stabbing him with his fully-grown claws and lifting him up high when questioning where they were. Deadpool, giving a witty remark instead of an answer, caused Wolverine to throw him on his knee. Deadpool, stating how his [[Earth-10005|world]] is doomed if they do not confront [[Mr. Paradox|Paradox]], insulted Wolverine for his deeds back in his own [[Mutant Genocide Universe|world]] when he said he did not care. Offended, Wolverine stabbed Deadpool in his back, only for Deadpool to shoot him in both of his sides when he flipped behind him and brought him to the ground. Wolverine thrusted his head back and threw him against the pruned {{WPS|20th Century Fox}} logo.
[[File:Wolverine & Deadpool in the Void.jpg|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine prepares to attack [[Sabretooth]]]]
In a standoff, Wolverine prepared his claws before charging at Deadpool while dodging his bullets. Wolverine then sliced the pistols in half with his claws, forcing Deadpool to use his [[Deadpool's Katanas|katanas]] and "baby knife" to stab Wolverine, these items being pierced through Wolverine's body. Wolverine was halted from decapitating Deadpool with the promise of having the [[TVA]] fix his world if they cooperate. Their attention was called to a cloaked figure, [[Human Torch/Void-Analyzing Fantastic Four|Johnny Storm]], whom alerted them of an approaching team of [[Cassandra Nova's Henchmen|someone's henchmen]]. This included a [[Glossary#Variant|Variant]] of [[Sabretooth]], who challenged Wolverine. Deadpool spruced Wolverine up from the fight they had for the moment people have been waiting decades for. Telling Deadpool to shut up, Wolverine charged towards Sabretooth, beheading him with his claws. Despite their efforts, Wolverine, Deadpool and Storm, who failed to fight [[Pyro]] as the Human Torch, were captured and taken to a [[Cassandra Nova's Lair|compound]]. Wolverine and Deadpool were informed by Storm of the Void's basics; facing [[Alioth]] or working for "[[Cassandra Nova|her]]," and about a [[Resistance]] with a [[Hero Hideout|hideout]] in the Borderlands.{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Escape from Cassandra Nova's Lair|Escape from Cassandra Nova]]====
[[File:The Wolverine.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine heading towards his escape]]
{{Quote|If there's a chance [[Resistance|they]] know how to get out of [[Void (End of Time)|here]], we find them and make those [[Time Variance Authority|TVA]] fuckers fix my shit like you fucking promised."<br>"I smell quest.|Wolverine and [[Deadpool]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Arriving at the [[Cassandra Nova's Lair|compound]], Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] saw a balded figure resembling [[Hub:Charles Xavier|Charles Xavier]] exit [[Giant-Man/Giant-Man Pruned|Giant-Man]]'s skull. Wolverine debunked the person being Xavier, yet not believing that she was [[Professor X/Cassandra Nova Birthed|Xavier]]'s pruned twin [[Cassandra Nova]]. Upon freeing them, Deadpool twisted [[Johnny Storm]]'s words about Nova. With her telepathic powers, Nova skinned Storm alive, and Wolverine faulted Deadpool for it. Though Deadpool proceeded to ask for Nova's help, Nova sought for an alliance with Wolverine, given their backstories and pruning. Going on to talk about her Xavier, she asked Wolverine if [[Professor X/Mutant Genocide|his]] also made him feel "safe." Replying that [[mutants]] are never safe, Wolverine attacked Nova and was sunk into the ground. After Nova uncovered Deadpool's memories by phasing her hand through his head, Wolverine stabbed her from behind, though he was simply pushed back. Upon [[Alioth]]'s approach, Wolverine enabled a nearby [[Sentinels|metal suit]]'s rocket boot to fly away, with Deadpool latching onto him.
[[File:Wolverine laughs at Wade.png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Logan laughing about [[Wade Wilson|Wilson]]'s toupee]]
Wolverine and Deadpool landed on a cliff, Deadpool forcing his baby knife out of Wolverine's buttocks. Wolverine instigated a rule; only he talks, despite Deadpool doubting the rule. Wolverine planned to get back to [[Paradox]] by finding the [[Resistance]] Storm mentioned earlier, enlist their help with their escape and threaten the [[TVA]] into fixing his [[Mutant Genocide Universe|world]]. Wolverine then spotted a [[Joe's Diner|diner]] from afar, in which he would search for anything with alcohol in it. Sitting by an unmasked Wilson, Logan questioned the few spots of hair stapled on his head. Wilson replied that he wore a toupee that nobody knew of, causing Logan to snicker and to assure him that everybody knew. Wilson then asked for his backstory before a third act flashback would explain it, Logan telling him to go fuck himself. Wilson talked about how his [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|version of the Wolverine]] was regarded as a hero, "''the'' [[X-Men/Earth-10005|X-Man]]," only for Logan to say he was not in his own.
[[File:Wolverine, Dogpool & Wade Wilson.jpg|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] finding [[Dogpool]]]]
Continuing their travels to the Borderlands, Wolverine asked Deadpool what exactly happened to his Wolverine; Deadpool detailing his sacrifice to save his young clone named [[X-23]]. Deadpool went on to tell him that, per [[Blind Al]], pain teaches people who they are, with Wolverine only remarking Blind Al's name. The two were met by a [[Dogs|dog]] that "[[Nicepool]]," a member of the hostile [[Deadpool Corps]] that ran after the dog, named [[Mary Puppins]], otherwise known as Dogpool. Wolverine asked Nicepool for directions to the Borderlands, and Nicepool told them to head towards the west and offered them the ''[[Ol' Betsy]]'' {{WPS|Honda Odyssey}} to travel in.{{Ref|DW}}

====Meeting the Resistance====
[[File:Wolverine (D&W).jpg|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine prepares to attack [[Deadpool]]]]
{{Quote|You know what you're a fucking joke. No wonder the [[Avengers]] didn't take you, or the [[X-Men/Earth-10005|X-Men]], and they'll take fuckin' anyone. I mean, you are a ridiculous, immature, half-wit moron. I have never met a sadder, more attention-starved, jabbering little prick in my entire life. And that says a lot 'cause I've been alive for more than two hundred fucking years.|Wolverine to [[Deadpool]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
On their way to the [[Hero Hideout]], Wolverine constantly told [[Deadpool]] to quit talking about his [[Wolverine Suit|suit]] and doing the gestures he made. Wolverine was questioned what the first thing he will do "if" his world is fixed, prompting Wolverine to abruptly step on the ''[[Ol' Betsy]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s brakes. Coming to the conclusion that Deadpool was lying the whole time and that he had no idea if the TVA could "fix" his [[Mutant Genocide Universe|world]], Wolverine stabbed Deadpool in his leg. Deadpool yelped, exclaiming that he made an "educated wish" as he needed Wolverine to save his friends back in [[Earth-10005]]. Wolverine hinged on his mention of an "educated wish," delivering a prolonged and especially insulting speech to upset Deadpool. He left Deadpool speechless until the latter stated that he would fight him, which Wolverine scoffed at. He was, however, punched in the face. Wolverine punched back, engaging in a [[Duel in Ol' Betsy|duel]] inside the car.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (105).png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Logan gargles [[Gambit]]'s liquor]]
The two fought for several hours until they both got tired and were driven to the [[Hero Hideout]] in their sleep. Deadpool awakened while a drunk Logan chugged down a bottle of beer he found. Upon the introductions of [[Elektra/Forgotten Elektra|Elektra]], [[Blade/Universe Defender Blade|Blade]] and [[Gambit]], Wolverine's bottle, belonging to Gambit, was shattered by the owner's playing card. Wolverine simply threw the broken bottle away in exchange for another. Deadpool asked by whom they were brought to the hideout, leading to [[X-23]]'s introduction, Logan's alternate daughter whom called herself Laura. Deadpool also learned of the [[Resistance]]'s fallen teammates, which included [[Human Torch/Void-Analyzing Fantastic Four|Johnny Storm]]. While Deadpool assured them he was still thriving, Logan believed that he had been in utter pain where he was still alive. Nonetheless, Deadpool gets the Resistance on board with fighting for their home universes by making [[Cassandra Nova]] help them escape the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]] by planting [[Juggernaut]]'s [[Juggernaut's Helmet|helmet]] onto her head. Logan told them they were all goners.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (64).png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Logan tells [[Laura]] his backstory]]
That night, Wolverine sat by a fire outside the hideout and was joined by Laura, who told him she noticed he shared the same mannerisms as the [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Logan]] she knew. Despite her stating he was a good man, Logan was convinced he was not, telling Laura of his many wrongdoings that got many people, such as the [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Men]], killed. Logan refused joining the Resistance, heading for [[Cassandra Nova's Lair]] by sunup, and told Laura that they have got the wrong guy. Laura stated that he always was the "wrong guy."{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Assault on Cassandra Nova's Lair|Escaping the Void]]====
[[File:Resistance Assemble.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine stands alongside the [[Resistance]]]]
{{Quote|I know your [[Professor X/Cassandra Nova Birthed|brother]]. As much I wanna fucking kill you, every bone in my body wants to fucking kill you! [[Professor X/Mutant Genocide|He]] would not let me stand here and watch you die. Take [[Deadpool|your]] hands off. This is for him. This is for Charles.|Wolverine to [[Cassandra Nova]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Wolverine joined the [[Resistance]] on their mission, and sat in the trunk of ''[[Ol' Betsy]]'' as they drove the next day. Once they barged through [[Cassandra Nova]]'s [[Cassandra Nova's Lair|lair]], Wolverine exited the trunk and stood alongside the team as Nova's [[Cassandra Nova's Henchmen|henchmen]] surrounded them. Wolverine commented on the Resistance's chances of survival, but [[Gambit]] told him to let people know about their battle.
[[File:Cassandra's finger in Logan's forehead.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine is subdued by [[Cassandra Nova]]]]
The two sides charged at each other, with Wolverine briefly fighting against [[Lady Deathstrike]], until the Resistance made their way through to the other side. Wolverine and Deadpool went inside as the rest of the Resistance stayed outside to fight. Wolverine and Deadpool confronted Nova, who had been expecting them, and she flicked Deadpool away. Wolverine tried to attack Nova, but she manipulated him to force his claws into the floor. Wolverine's mind was infiltrated by Nova, who put her finger through his head.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (39).png|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine inside of his own mind]]
Inside of his mind, Wolverine found himself amidst the graves of those he had killed during his rampage. Nova joined him, commenting on Wolverine hiding behind his anger to cover up for his guilt. Wolverine fell to his knees and opened up about how he let down the [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Men]], which led to his murderous rampage. Wolverine revealed that he wanted to be the person [[Professor X/Mutant Genocide|Professor X]] thought he could be, so Nova told him he could be whoever he wanted in the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]].
[[File:Wolverine convinces Nova.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine gets through to [[Cassandra Nova]]]]
Nova silenced the voices haunting Wolverine, which gave him some relief. Nova attempted to comfort Wolverine, but at that moment he exposed the trap that she fell into, as Deadpool put [[Juggernaut]]'s [[Juggernaut's Helmet|helmet]] on her head, disabling her powers. Deadpool ordered Nova to send them home, but she refused, so Wolverine and Deadpool argued over which one of them would kill Nova. [[Pyro]] shot Nova in the stomach and began giving a speech, but Wolverine punched him, knocking Pyro out.
[[File:Deadpool and Wolverine jumping into a portal.png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] escape the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]]]]
Realizing that Nova was dying, Wolverine told Deadpool to remove the helmet from her, but Deadpool was unsure. Wolverine stated that he wore his [[Wolverine Suit|suit]] to prove that he was an X-Man, and that Professor X would not let him allow Nova to die. Wolverine then removed the helmet and told Nova that Professor X would have searched for her if he knew of her existence. Nova decided to help them escape by opening a [[Inter-Dimensional Portal|portal]] to [[Earth-10005]], and Wolverine and Deadpool jumped through before [[Alioth]] arrived.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Everyone (18).png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] enter [[Earth-10005]]]]
Wolverine and Deadpool crash-landed upon the {{WPS|Kia Carnival}} Deadpool's friend [[Peter Wisdom]] was selling to the Chipman family at [[Drive Max]]. One of the children recognized Wolverine, Deadpool joking that [[Walt Disney Studios]] is going to have [[Hugh Jackman]] portraying him till he becomes ninety years old. Wolverine and Deadpool subsequently left.{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Attack on Earth-10005|Fighting the Deadpool Corps]]====
[[File:Deadpool questions Paradox.png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] find [[Mr. Paradox]]]]
{{Quote|Are you ready?"<br>"I get to kill a [[Deadpool Corps|hundred yous]]? Fuck, yeah, I'm ready.|[[Deadpool]] and Wolverine|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] confronted [[Paradox]] at the entrance to the subway where he was guarding the [[Time Ripper]], only for a [[Inter-Dimensional Portal|second portal]] to open behind them, with [[Pyro]] emerging from it and trying to warn Paradox before being killed by [[Cassandra Nova|Nova]]. Nova then delved into Paradox's mind, discovered the Time Ripper and decided to use it for her own gain, before telekinetically pushing the two mutants back into a [[Liefeld's|foot cream establishment]].
[[File:Wolverine & Dogpool.jpg|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine shields himself with [[Dogpool]]]]
Upon recovering, the duo saw [[Dogpool]] and [[Nicepool]] exit the portal, but Logan subsequently smelled a large number of Deadpool's scents also coming from the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]]. As the [[Deadpool Corps]] came to the streets in full force, Wade forced Wolverine to hold Dogpool while he tried to reason his other variants working for Nova. The alternate [[Hub:Wade Wilson|Deadpools]] didn't listen to reason and started shooting in the crowd. Hiding behind a car to escape the bullets, Wolverine accused Deadpool of having used Nicepool as a human shield, the latter proving to be devoid of healing factor. Deadpool tried to reach a donut stand under the pretext that there were surgical kits, but Wolverine had already understood that Deadpool just wanted to use Nicepool as a human shield again. Following Nicepool's head exploding, Wolverine used Dogpool to dissuade the Deadpools from shooting him while he joined his Deadpool behind the stand. The duo briefly ranted about Nicepool's fate, with Deadpool taking the opportunity to retrieve his golden guns, then asked Wolverine if he was ready to fight, to which Wolverine responded that he was totally ready to kill hundreds of Deadpool [[Glossary#V|Variants]].
[[File:Deadpool&Wolverine.png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] defeat the [[Deadpool Corps]]]]
Facing the Deadpool Corps, Wolverine put on his hidden mask, much to the astonishment of Deadpool, who thought that he kept the mask for special occasions, and Wolverine replied that he mainly puts it on for killing mostly. Gun and claws out, Wolverine and Deadpool rushed at the variants and quickly massacred most of them in a bloody manner while taking wounds themselves that did not stop them. They are briefly pushed back but quickly regain their initial upper hand and eliminate the last Deadpools inside a bus, before practically exiting through the rear window, Wolverine landing but Deadpool missing on his side. As soon as they noticed [[Babypool]] laughing at them, they watched their victims regenerate afterwards, then were surrounded by them. Suddenly, [[Peter Wisdom]] joined the scene, the Deadpool Corps having recognized him since they also had a Peter in their universe, completely diverted their attention to him, so Wolverine and Deadpool took advantage of the inattention to enter the subway.{{Ref|DW}}

====Saving All Timelines====
[[File:Threatening Mr Paradox.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine threatens [[Paradox]]]]
{{Quote|You got a whole world to get back to. I got nothing. Give me this."<br>"Hey. I waited a long time for this team-up. Y'know something? You're the ''best'' [[Hub:Logan|Wolverine]].|Wolverine and [[Deadpool]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Entering the subway station, Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] met [[Paradox]], distressed over [[Cassandra Nova]]'s plan to destroy all universes except the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]]. Wolverine asked him how to shut the [[Time Ripper]] down, forcing Paradox onto the control panel when he said he did not know. Deadpool remarked on the intimidation his mask exuded, comparing it to {{WPS|Batman}}'s. Paradox explained that the Time Ripper was fed by matter and anti-matter feeds, and Nova was redirecting the Time Ripper's power to exterminate every timeline. The only way to destroy the Time Ripper was to create a circuit between the two feeds, although whoever created the circuit would be atomized, despite the duo's regenerative healing factors.
[[File:Wolverine and Deadpool hold hands.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine creates a circuit with [[Deadpool]]]]
Approaching the feeds' chamber below, Wolverine halted Deadpool to repeat Paradox's words on the inevitability of a sacrifice. Deadpool decided that he would be the circuit because he brought Wolverine into the mess and lied to his face. Wolverine echoed Deadpool's mention of an "educated wish," stating that it must be him, seeing as Deadpool had a world to get back to while he did not. Wolverine opened the chamber's door but was pushed outside by Deadpool, who sacrificed himself instead. With one feed in hand, Deadpool reached for the other as Wolverine tried to barge through the door. With time running out and Deadpool not being able to reach the second feed, Wolverine managed to break through the door and grab the second feed in his claws, grabbing Deadpool's hand with his and effectively creating the circuit. The energy from the feeds caused the part of his [[Wolverine Suit|suit]] that covered his upper body to explode, exposing his abs. Wolverine reminisced about his past and the person he had become as he screamed until the Time Ripper exploded, killing Nova in the process.
[[File:Deadpool and Wolverine Slow-Mo Walk.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] exit the chamber unharmed]]
When [[Paradox]]'s boss, [[Hunter B-15]], appeared on the scene, he tried to make it seem like he did nothing wrong and that Wolverine and Deadpool had sacrificed themselves, but his lie was revealed when the duo exited the chamber unharmed. Logan handed his mask to [[Ralph]], who stared blindingly at his pecs, which Deadpool covered up with a [[TVA]] jacket. Deadpool explained that they survived thanks to the power of a Deadpool and a Wolverine listening to {{WPS|Madonna}}'s "{{WPS|Like a Prayer}}". Despite the reckless actions of Deadpool, bringing an Omega-level [[mutant]] into his timeline, B-15 showed Logan and Deadpool that the [[Earth-10005]] timeline was growing back, advising them to rest before they'd be called. Deadpool joked that Logan would be portrayed by [[Hugh Jackman]] until the latter turned ninety. Besides asking for the [[Resistance]] to be returned to their home universes, Deadpool also requested for Logan's actions back in his world to be undone. However, B-15 declined the latter request, as Logan became a better man due to his experiences in his [[Mutant Genocide Universe|universe]] and they allow him to stay in Deadpool's universe. Deadpool invited him to get food, something Wolverine agreed to.{{Ref|DW}}

===New World, New Life===
====Celebrating Victory====
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Everyone (11).png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|[[Wade Wilson|Wilson]] introduces Logan to [[Blind Al]]]]{{Quote|Give me the fucking [[Dogpool|dog]], talk to the [[Vanessa Carlysle|girl]].|Logan to [[Wade Wilson]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
While eating shawarma with [[Deadpool]], the pair witnessed the city being repaired before [[Dogpool]] came up to them, leading Deadpool to adopt her as his pet. When Deadpool remarked that the [[Avengers]] created shawarma, Logan stated that they would have been fortunate to have him before he was asked on what he would do now, as Logan stated he was unsure what to do now in this new world, though he stated he would figure something out. As Logan was leaving, Deadpool stopped him and invited him to his [[Wade Wilson's Apartment|apartment]]. He was introduced to [[Blind Al]] and hung out with Wilson's friends. Noticing Deadpool staring at his ex-girlfriend [[Vanessa Carlysle]], he instructed him to give him Dogpool so that Wilson could talk to Vanessa while he spoke with [[Laura]], who had chosen to stay with him.{{Ref|DW}}{{Clear}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
{{Quote|If you want to kill me, it's going to take more than a [[Baby Knife|little blade]]."<br>"How about six? {{WPS|Good Will Hunting|My boy's wicked strong}}.|[[Cassandra Nova]] and [[Deadpool]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''Mutant Physiology''': As a [[mutant]], Logan possesses various paranormal traits, his specific mutation granting him animalistic characteristics such as advanced senses, heightened instincts and retractable bone claws, as well as superhuman physical attributes and regenerative capabilities that render him nearly immortal.
**'''Superhuman Strength''': [[File:Wolverine lifts Deadpool.png|thumb|250px|Wolverine lifting [[Deadpool]]]] Logan has demonstrated many great feats of strength, effortlessly lifting [[Deadpool]] into the air and hurling him through concrete barriers. He was able to ram a [[Ol' Betsy|minivan]] with his bare body with such force to trigger its airbags and send it backwards. He also was able to deform and break down a metal blast door with his bare hands.
**'''Superhuman Durability''': A combination of his healing factor and [[adamantium]] coated skeleton allows Logan to recover quickly from any damage without long-lasting, debilitating effects. This ability extends to his internal organs such as his liver, allowing him to drink copious amounts of alcohol and rubbing alcohol and merely becoming slightly intoxicated from its alcoholic content. Logan was also submerged in the soil for an extended period of time by [[Cassandra Nova]] and emerged harmlessly.
**'''Superhuman Agility''': Logan possesses enhanced agility beyond the capability of an ordinary [[Humans|human being]]. He is able to pounce and dodge attacks with little effort.
**'''Superhuman Stamina''': Logan's healing factor provides him with some immunity to fatigue as a result of physical exertion. He was able to fight with Deadpool while enduring numerous injuries for hours before succumbing to exhaustion.
**'''Superhuman Reflexes''': [[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Go (1).png|thumb|250px|Wolverine dodging [[Deadpool]]'s attack]] Logan is able to effortlessly dodge melee attacks at a greater rate of success than a normal human being.
**'''Enhanced Senses''': Logan possess enhanced mutant senses, particularly, a keen sense of smell. While in the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]], Logan was able to smell [[Sabretooth]]'s presence and detected the presence of food in an abandoned [[Joe's Diner|diner]] hundreds of meters away. While on [[Earth-10005|Earth-10005]], Logan was able to detect hundreds of Deadpool variants before they came out of an [[Inter-Dimensional Portal]].
**'''Regenerative Healing Factor''': Logan does not suffer from long-term effects of many injuries. Stab wounds, impalement, gunshot wounds, burns and even matter-antimatter annihilation are little to no threat to him as he will heal with no lingering signs in mere seconds.
**'''Longevity''': A byproduct of his healing factor, Logan's aging process has been decelerated. He has lived since the early 19th century, noting to be over two hundred years old, he still possesses the overall look, health, and vitality of a man in his prime.
**[[File:Wolverine Claws Out.jpg|thumb|250px|Wolverine with his [[adamantium]] claws out]]'''Retractable Claws''': Logan has a pair of three, 12-inch retractable [[adamantium]] coated claws in each forearm which extend between each of his fingers' knuckles.
**'''Psychic Resistance''': Logan was able to resist the telepathic effects of Cassandra Nova, being able to simultaneously see his memories and the real world and distracting her for long enough to be subdued by Deadpool.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|You don't want this.|Logan to [[Deadpool]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (45).png|thumb|250px|Wolverine fighting against [[Deadpool]]]]
*'''Master Combatant''': Logan is a fiercely skilled fighter with decades of experience. He overpowered and nearly decapitated [[Deadpool]], who served in the Special Forces. While he is very aggressive in a fight, he can also strategize to counter specific opponents; when he [[Duel in the Void|first fought]] Deadpool, he used his claws to slash his Desert Eagles to force him to fight at a closer distance. When Deadpool trapped his claws with his swords, he simply retracted his claws to free himself and continue his assault. In their second fight, Logan and a now serious Deadpool fought for several hours with no victor emerging. Logan also swiftly defeated and killed [[Sabretooth]].
*'''Master Acrobat''': With his agility, Wolverine has proven to be very skilled at fighting in mid-air and used it to land devastating attacks, as seen in the raid on Nova's headquarters.

