==Trivia==
*In the comics, '''James Howlett''' is an anti-heroic [[mutant]] who joined the [[X-Men]] despite his brutal and ruthless methods to have justice done, though he is at his core a good person and has been part of other superhero teams such as the [[Fantastic Four]] or the [[Avengers]].
*Wolverine is listed as one of the default names on ''[[The Avengers: Skrull Takedown]]'''s high score screen.
*''[[She-Hulk: Attorney at Law]]'' features two references to Wolverine:
**While [[Jennifer Walters]] searches for new jobs on a blog site in the episode ''[[Superhuman Law]]'', a headline for an article about a sighting of a man who had recently fought in a bar brawl and sported metal claws can be seen.
**During the end credits sequence of the episode ''[[Mean, Green, and Straight Poured into These Jeans]]'', artwork of [[Augustus Pugliese]] showcasing his sneaker collection to [[Nikki Ramos]] features a depiction of the classic [[Wolverine Suit]].
*Wolverine's claws are made of [[Adamantium]]. Because of this metal alloy's association with the character, {{WPS|20th Century Studios|20th Century Fox}} had its film rights for the {{WPS|X-Men (film series)|''X-Men'' film series}} back when ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'' was being developed and thus forced the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] to have [[Ultron]] be built of [[Vibranium]] instead of Adamantium like in the comics, even though Ultron was created before Wolverine.
*In {{WPS|20th Century Studios|20th Century Fox}}'s {{WPS|X-Men (film series)|''X-Men'' film series}}, Wolverine's claws come out in between his knuckles instead of over them. This continuity detail was kept for ''[[Deadpool & Wolverine]]''.
*The appearance of Wolverine's [[Wolverine Suit|suit]] in ''[[Deadpool & Wolverine]]'' marks the first time the character has been depicted with a design faithful to the comics in live-action. The suit's aesthetics specifically derive from the character's appearance in ''Astonishing X-Men'' (2004-08) by [[Joss Whedon]] and [[John Cassaday]].
*When [[Cassandra Nova]] enters Wolverine's mind, stock footage from {{WPS|20th Century Studios|20th Century Fox}}'s {{WPS|X-Men (film series)|''X-Men'' film series}} was used for flashes of memories, also including ''{{WPS|X2 (film)|X2}}'' and ''{{WPS|Logan (film)|Logan}}'', despite these being experiences of [[Earth-10005|Earth-10005]]'s [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]], implying this Wolverine experienced them as well.
*In ''[[The Art of Deadpool & Wolverine]]'', Wolverine and [[Deadpool]] bicker as they write all over the book.<ref>''[[The Art of Deadpool & Wolverine]]''</ref>

==Behind the Scenes==
*Wolverine in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] is the second live-action incarnation of the character, following an [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|incarnation]] also portrayed by [[Hugh Jackman]] with {{WPS|Troye Sivan}} as a younger James Howlett in {{WPS|20th Century Studios|20th Century Fox}}'s {{WPS|X-Men (film series)|''X-Men'' film series}}.
*In 2015, [[Hugh Jackman]] stated that he planned to retire from playing Wolverine in 2017 with ''{{WPS|Logan (film)|Logan}}'', which was developed as Jackman's final outing as the character.<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-33688933 Hugh Jackman asks for ideas from fans for his final outing as Wolverine]</ref> However, [[Ryan Reynolds (actor)|Ryan Reynolds]] often approached him to return for the role one more time so they could make a Wolverine-[[Deadpool]] crossover, as Jackman had enjoyed the first ''{{WPS|Deadpool (film)|Deadpool}}'' film. Around 2022, Jackman finally decided to call Reynolds during a family road trip just as Reynolds prepared to meet with [[Marvel Studios]] president [[Kevin Feige]] to discuss ''[[Deadpool & Wolverine]]'', which led to Jackman joining the project to reprise his role as Wolverine for one more film.<ref>[https://variety.com/2022/film/features/hugh-jackman-dad-death-the-son-wolverine-1235413831/ The Story of Hugh Jackman in Five Acts]</ref> Jackman initially retired because he felt the role was too demanding around 2013, but since 2017, he had had a break from it and done other things like dance or stage shows, making him find it really fun to return as Wolverine.<ref>[https://people.com/ryan-reynolds-hugh-jackman-secret-sauce-friendship-exclusive-8654857 Ryan Reynolds and Hugh Jackman: The ''Deadpool & Wolverine'' Stars Reveal 'Secret Sauce' to Their 17-Year Friendship]</ref>
**Upon announcing the film, Reynolds and Jackman quickly assured fans that despite Jackman's early promise to retire from Wolverine, ''Deadpool & Wolverine'' will not retcon the emotional events of ''{{WPS|Logan (film)|Logan}}'', claiming that the former film takes place before the latter's 2029 setting;<ref>[https://variety.com/2022/film/news/ryan-reynolds-wolverine-deadpool-3-separate-logan-dead-1235386650/ Wolverine in ‘Deadpool 3’ Is ‘Totally Separate’ from ‘Logan,’ Ryan Reynolds Confirms: ‘Logan Died’ and We’re ‘Not Touching That’]</ref> Jackman even reached out to ''Logan'' writer-director {{WPS|James Mangold}} to inform him that their film would not be contradicted in any ways, as he felt it was important to preserve the finality of ''Logan''.<ref>[https://theplaylist.net/hugh-jackman-says-wolverine-hates-deadpool-wants-to-punch-him-in-the-face-in-deadpool-3-20221224/ Hugh Jackman Says Wolverine “Hates” Deadpool & “Wants To Punch Him” In The Face In ‘Deadpool 3’]</ref> Feige was actually nervous over seeing Jackman back in the role and he advised him to not come back to "undo" the ending of ''Logan'', but accepted Jackman's insistence after a long drive to return once he pointed out that the Wolverine he would play wouldn't be exactly the same ''Logan'' one.<ref>[https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/deadpool-wolverine-hugh-jackman-sides-we-havent-seen-before-exclusive/ Hugh Jackman Teases ‘Sides Of Wolverine We Haven’t Seen Before’ In Deadpool & Wolverine – Exclusive]</ref> In order for Wolverine to return, Jackman said that Marvel Studios came up with [[Time Travel|a plot device]] to move around the timelines and not mess the continuity of Fox's films.<ref>[https://variety.com/2022/film/news/hugh-jackman-wolverine-deadpool-3-logan-timeline-1235466229/ Hugh Jackman Says Wolverine in ‘Deadpool 3’ Won’t Screw With ‘Logan’ Timeline: ‘That Was Important to Me’]</ref>
*[[Anthony Russo|Anthony]] and [[Joe Russo]] have stated, had {{WPS|The Walt Disney Company}} acquired {{WPS|20th Century Studios|20th Century Fox}} and thus regained the ''X-Men'' film rights prior to the development of ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'', they would have had Wolverine leading a [[mutant]] team against [[Thanos]] and would have killed off all of Wolverine's teammates minus himself with the [[Snap]] to have a bloodthirsty Wolverine go after Thanos.<ref>[https://latam.ign.com/avengers-endgame/62246/feature/avengers-endgame-la-razon-por-la-que-wolverine-seria-el-unico-x-men-en-sobrevivir-al-chasquido-de-th Avengers: Endgame - la razón por la que Wolverine sería el único X-Men en sobrevivir al chasquido de Thanos]</ref>
*[[Hugh Jackman]]'s diet to develop the right physique for ''[[Deadpool & Wolverine]]'' involved him consuming eight thousand calories per day.<ref>[https://variety.com/2023/film/news/hugh-jackman-wolverine-diet-8000-calories-deadpool-3-1235544557/ Hugh Jackman's Wolverine Diet: 8,000 Calories a Day for Deadpool 3 (variety.com)]</ref> Jackman acknowledged this process as the hardest part of returning as Wolverine, as he had to eat like five or six meals every day because his body type is naturally skinny.<ref>[https://people.com/hugh-jackman-hardest-part-of-being-wolverine-again-exclusive-8655772 Hugh Jackman Reveals the Hardest Part of Becoming Wolverine Again at 55 — and It Wasn’t the Crazy Workouts (Exclusive)]</ref>
*[[Daniel Stevens]] was a stunt double for [[Hugh Jackman]] in the role of Wolverine.

